item.title: Who Makes More Money - Monte Carlo Simulation?
item.description: I recently came across the following PDF University of Missouri Employee Salaries. This PDF contains salary information for over 20,000 University of Missouri employees. I wanted to see if I could accomplish the following: Parse the PDF into a format that I could analyze using Python Using each employees first name and/or middle name, make a “guess” on their gender Use a statistical test to determine whether a certain gender makes more money on average Part 1: Parsing the PDF I used the following notebook to parse the PDF, Parse PDF.
